## Adding a New Theme

### 1. Create Theme File

`themes/custom/yourtheme.ts`:
```typescript
import { Theme } from "../types"

export const yourTheme: Theme = {
  name: "your-theme",
  label: "Your Theme",
  description: "Theme description",
  category: "custom",
  icon: "Star",
  radius: "0.5rem",
  colors: {
    background: "210 100% 98%",
    foreground: "210 100% 10%",
    primary: "200 100% 50%",
    // ... all required colors
  },
}
```

### 2. Register in `themes/index.ts`

```typescript
import { yourTheme } from "./custom/yourtheme"

export const themes: ThemeRegistry = {
  // ... existing themes
  "your-theme": yourTheme,
}
```

### 3. Generate CSS and add to `app/globals.css`

```typescript
import { generateThemeCSS } from "@/themes"
const css = generateThemeCSS(yourTheme)
```

### 4. Update ThemeProvider in `app/layout.tsx`

```typescript
<ThemeProvider
  themes={["light", "dark", "system", "ocean", "forest", "midnight", "your-theme"]}
  // ...
>
```

## Color Format

HSL without commas:
```css
--primary: 217 91% 60%;  /* Correct */
/* NOT: hsl(217, 91%, 60%) */
```

## Required Color Variables

Every theme must define:
- `background`, `foreground`
- `card`, `card-foreground`
- `primary`, `primary-foreground`
- `secondary`, `secondary-foreground`
- `muted`, `muted-foreground`
- `accent`, `accent-foreground`
- `destructive`, `destructive-foreground`
- `border`, `input`, `ring`

## Theme Utilities

```typescript
import { getAllThemes, getTheme, getThemesByCategory, validateTheme } from "@/themes"

getAllThemes()                    // All themes
getTheme("ocean")                 // Specific theme
getThemesByCategory("custom")     // Themes by category
validateTheme(newTheme)           // Validate structure
```

## Using Theme Colors

```tsx
// Tailwind classes
<div className="bg-background text-foreground">
<div className="bg-primary text-primary-foreground">
<div className="border-border">

// Custom CSS
.element {
  background-color: hsl(var(--primary));
  color: hsl(var(--primary-foreground));
}
```

## Conditional Theme Styling

```typescript
"use client"
import { useTheme } from "next-themes"

function Component() {
  const { resolvedTheme } = useTheme()
  const isDark = resolvedTheme === "dark"
  // ...
}
```

## Disabling Theme Switching

Set fixed theme in `app/layout.tsx`:
```typescript
<ThemeProvider
  defaultTheme="light"
  forcedTheme="light"
  enableSystem={false}
>
```
